    },
    {
      "id": "859e82706727e4797b785b96cc66ec43748df1fa",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-03-14 01:03:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThis patch ended up with OOM in my performance benchmark. Temporarily deny it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "9f0b50cf047e15034f707e49914c4bc56854c299",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 124,
        "name": "Prakash Surya",
        "email": "lists@prakashsurya.com",
        "username": "prakash"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-14 16:53:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nJinshan, do you think it was a result of calls to ll_releasepage not being able to acquire an env, because another thread is holding that CPUs env?\n\nIf so, we can try using the normal interfaces to get an env if the per cpu interface fails. That would ensure ll_releasepage can always get an env, but it might be slow if the per cpu call fails.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "b5b84ce13ad042b89cd1febb3b5ba48e28ffc88c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-03-14 18:05:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: No score\n\nIt turned out to be very slow because I tried to run the patch of \"Remove the global cl_env list\" also and I saw OOM as well.\n\nI also tried to work out a patch to use static percpu env but the problem is that cl_page_put() can sleep which makes percpu array totally useless. I will push my update to this patch but unfortunately we can't land it.\n\nIt seems like we have to go back to my original way to reduce the contention of global env list.\n\nHowever, these patches are still useful. There will be a project named \"simplify clio stack\"  and I will revise ll_releasepage() to not sleep and then these patches can be applied.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "d029af4840a76f003aa3028cf3c46ba072748824",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 124,
        "name": "Prakash Surya",
        "email": "lists@prakashsurya.com",
        "username": "prakash"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-14 18:23:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThat's interesting how you saw OOMs with the \"remove list\" patch. We've been running with that on Sequoia for some time, and haven't seen issues from that patch.\n\nWhat kind of test are you running to trigger the failure?\n\nThe global list definitely wont work for us on Sequoia. The single global lock brings the system to a halt with 66 CPUs in each IO node.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "c788ac3175700abd8e257f78b1c9e7b44c299630",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-03-14 21:21:10.000000000",
